# Executive Summary

TOVE Leeds requires a comprehensive cloud-based compliance and certification management system to streamline their inspection, assessment, training, and NDT services. The system will replace manual processes with automated workflows, enhance traceability, improve accuracy, and ensure compliance management across all departments.

The solution comprises a unified platform with web portals and Tablet applications serving multiple user roles including clients, inspectors, trainers, supervisors, accountants, and management. The system will manage the complete lifecycle from service requests to certificate issuance, renewals, and compliance tracking.

## Business Objectives

- Automate certificate generation, result approvals, and data storage processes
- Enhance stakeholder access control and data security
- Improve operational efficiency through real-time data management
- Ensure regulatory compliance and audit readiness
- Provide comprehensive analytics and reporting capabilities
- Enable mobile accessibility for field operations

## Expected Benefits

- Reduced processing time for certificates and renewals by 70%
- Improved data accuracy and elimination of manual errors
- Enhanced client satisfaction through self-service capabilities
- Real-time visibility into operations and performance metrics
- Streamlined payment processing and financial tracking
- Mobile-first approach for field inspector productivity

# Project Overview

## Background

TOVE Leeds operates in the compliance and certification industry, providing equipment inspections, operator assessments, training services, and Non-Destructive Testing (NDT) services. The current manual and paper-based processes result in inefficiencies, delays in certificate issuance, and challenges in maintaining accurate records and compliance tracking.

The organization requires a modern, cloud-based solution that can handle the complexity of their operations while providing seamless access to stakeholders through web portals and Tablet applications.

## Project Objectives

- Develop a centralized cloud-based platform for all compliance and certification activities
- Implement role-based access control (advance level) ensuring data security and operational integrity
- Automate workflows from service requests to certificate issuance and renewals
- Provide real-time Tablet access for field inspectors and assessors
- Enable comprehensive reporting and analytics for management decision-making
- Integrate payment processing and accounting functionalities
- Support multi-language capabilities (English, Arabic, Urdu, Hindi, Bengali) for diverse user base.

## Project Scope

**In Scope**

- Web-based portals for all user roles with different dashboards.
- Native mobile applications for iOS and Android with can work both offline and online.
- Complete workflow automation for inspections, assessments, and training and NDT services.
- Certificate generation, verification (QR code, web, mobile application) and renewal processes.
- Payment processing and financial management and integration with existing Odoo ERP system.
- Comprehensive (daily, weekly, monthly and yearly) reporting and analytics dashboard.
- Multi-language support (English, Arabic, Urdu, Bangla, Hindi and other).
- Integration with third-party services (payment gateways, video conferencing).
- Cloud infrastructure deployment and hosting.
- Data migration from existing systems.
- User training, how-to-guides and system documentation.

**Out of Scope**

- Hardware procurement for client organizations
- Legacy system maintenance beyond data migration period
- Custom integrations with client-specific systems not mentioned in requirements
- On-premise deployment options
- Third-party software licensing costs not specified in technical requirements

# Stakeholders

| Stakeholder Role | Primary Responsibilities | System Access Level |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Clients | Request services, view, download, verify and export certificates in Pdf/image etc, submit renewals, make payments | Client Portal & Mobile App |

| NDT Technicians | Perform NDT testing, document results, submit reports | NDT Interface & Mobile App |

# System Architecture Overview

The TOVE Leeds Cloud-Based Compliance and Certification Management System follows a modern, scalable architecture designed to support multiple user interfaces, secure data management, and seamless integrations.

## Platform Components

- **Web Portals:** Role-based web interfaces for all user types
- **Mobile Applications:** Native iOS and Android apps for field operations and end user
- **Cloud Infrastructure:** Scalable cloud hosting with auto-scaling capabilities
- **Database Systems:** Secure, encrypted data storage with backup and recovery
- **API Gateway:** RESTful APIs for system integrations and mobile connectivity
- **File Storage:** Secure document and media storage with CDN distribution

## Integration Points

- Payment Gateway APIs for secure financial transactions
- Video Conferencing Integration (teams) for training sessions
- OCR Services for automated data extraction from documents
- SMS and Email Services for notifications
- Accounting System Integration for financial data export
- Third-party Authentication Services (OAuth2, Multi-Factor Authentication)

# Functional Requirements

## End-User Mobile Application (Tove Leeds App)

**FR-01: Home Screen & Navigation**

**Description:** The home screen serves as the primary navigation hub displaying user profile picture, name, all available tabs, notifications, and settings access.

**Requirements:**

- Display user profile picture and name prominently
- Show all accessible tabs based on user role and permissions
- Notification icon with badge count for unread notifications
- Settings icon in top right corner
- Quick access bottom navigation for core functions (Home, Scanner, Settings)
- Support for non-registered users with limited access to scanner and login functions

**FR-02: User Profile Management**

**Description:** Comprehensive profile management with controlled edit capabilities for different field types.

**Requirements:**

- Display fields: Name, ID Number, Email Address, Nationality, Date of Birth, Address, City, Country
- Restrict editing: Name, ID Number, and Date of Birth cannot be modified by users
- Editable fields: Mobile number, Email, Address, City, Country (with proper validation) and history of old record and option to retain from the admin side.
- Profile picture upload and change capability
- Administrative override capability for ID number changes with audit trail

**FR-03: My Digital Documents/Cards**

**Description:** Central repository for all digital certificates and operator cards issued to the user.

**Requirements:**

- Display all operator cards with titles (Mobile Crane, Forklift, Rigger Level 3, Fire Training, First Aid Training, etc.)
- Visual expiry indication: Red diagonal "EXPIRED" mark for expired certificates/card
- Card details: Issue date, expiry date, certificate number, verification codes
- Download capability for digital certificates/card
- QR code display for verification purposes
- Separate "Renew" button for each renewable certificate
- A certificate should only become eligible for renewal once the user has successfully completed the required CPD activities such as quizzes, cross-match exercises, or relevant assessment videos in accordance with FR-14 guidelines.

**FR-04: Payment Methods & Processing**

**Description:** Secure payment processing with multiple payment options and receipt generation.

**Requirements:**

- Support for direct bank transfers and payment gateway integration
- Secure payment form with validation
- Digital receipt generation with customized design
- Receipt details: Receipt number, date, name, ID number, service description, amount in figures and words
- Payment history tracking and status updates
- Failed payment notification and retry mechanism

**FR-05: Settings & Preferences**

**Description:** User customization and security settings management.

**Requirements:**

- Multi-language selection: English, Arabic, Urdu, Bangla, Hindi
- Face ID/Biometric authentication setup
- Theme selection (Light/Dark modes)
- Mobile number update via SMS verification
- Profile picture upload/change functionality
- Privacy and security settings
- Notification preferences configuration

**FR-06: Communication Preferences**

**Description:** Language and notification preferences for personalized communication.

**Requirements:**

- Language preference selection affecting all notifications and communications
- Notification types: New operator card, birthday wishes, expiry alerts, discounts, national day celebrations
- Delivery method preferences: Push notifications, email, SMS
- Frequency settings for different notification types

**FR-07: QR Code Scanner**

**Description:** Universal QR code scanning capability for certificate verification.

**Requirements:**

- QR code scanning for registered users to verify other persons' certificates
- Manual card number entry option as alternative to scanning
- Scanner access for non-registered users (limited functionality)
- Verification result display with certificate details
- Offline scanning capability with sync when online

**FR-08: Contact Us & Support**

**Description:** Comprehensive support and feedback system with multiple contact options.

**Requirements:**

- General inquiries and app-specific issue reporting
- Multiple contact methods: Website link, email, phone number
- Customized feedback form with issue categorization
- Third-party integration capability for advanced feedback analysis
- Ticket tracking system for support requests

**FR-09: Legal Information**

**Description:** Dynamic legal information management with administrative control.

**Requirements:**

- Legal document display with formatting support
- Administrative update capability without developer intervention
- Version control for legal document changes
- Option to link to external website for legal information
- Offline access to cached legal documents

**FR-10: Privacy Policy**

**Description:** Privacy policy management with similar capabilities to legal information.

**Requirements:**

- Privacy policy document display and management
- Administrative content management
- External website linking option
- User acknowledgment tracking for policy updates
- Multi-language privacy policy support

**FR-11: Social Media Integration**

**Description:** Social media connectivity for enhanced user engagement.

**Requirements:**

- Social media platform links: LinkedIn, Facebook, Instagram, X (Twitter), TikTok
- Deep linking to social media apps when installed
- Social sharing capabilities for achievements and certifications
- Social media login integration (optional)

**FR-12: Vlogs & Community Features (Optional)**

**Description:** User-generated content platform for training-related videos and community interaction.

**Requirements:**

- Video upload capability for training-related content
- Content moderation and approval workflow
- Commenting and interaction system
- Content categorization by training type
- User reputation and rating system

**FR-13: Coupon & Loyalty System**

**Description:** Comprehensive loyalty program with points and referral system.

**Requirements:**

- Point accumulation system for various activities
- Referral scheme with reward tracking
- Coupon generation and redemption
- Loyalty tier management
- Points-to-discount conversion system

**FR-14: Training Library & CPD**

**Description:** Comprehensive Continuing Professional Development (CPD) system with video content and assessments.

**Requirements:**

- Video library organized by certificate category
- Multiple choice questions and quiz system
- Cross-matching exercises and interactive content
- Progress tracking for CPD requirements
- Integration with YouTube and external video platforms
- Metadata management for content organization
- Completion certificates for CPD activities

**FR-15: Coupon History & Management**

**Description:** Complete coupon lifecycle management and reporting.

**Requirements:**

- Coupon categories: Sign-up, renewal, birthday, special occasions (Eid, National Day)
- Recommendation-based coupons from existing users and referral programs.
- Coupon status tracking: Valid, Used, Expired
- Detailed usage history with dates and services
- Comprehensive reporting: Weekly, monthly, yearly, custom date ranges
- Regional and ID-based coupon analytics

**FR-16: Purchasing History & Receipts**

**Description:** Complete transaction history with detailed digital receipts.

**Requirements:**

- Chronological listing of all cards and certificates purchased
- Customized digital receipt design with company branding
- Receipt information: Receipt number, date, name, ID number, service/certificate name, amount (figures and words), region
- Export capabilities (PDF, email)
- Search and filter functionality
- Reporting capabilities matching coupon system requirements

**FR-17: Review & Feedback System**

**Description:** Customer feedback collection and analysis system.

**Requirements:**

- Custom-designed feedback forms
- Rating system for services and instructors
- Optional integration with external survey platforms (SurveyMonkey, etc.)
- Feedback categorization and sentiment analysis
- Response tracking and follow-up capabilities

**FR-18: Certificate/Card Renewal Process**

**Description:** Streamlined renewal process with CPD integration.

**Requirements:**

- CPD requirement tracking for each certificate type
- Content completion verification (videos, quizzes, assessments)
- Automatic renewal button activation upon CPD completion
- Payment integration (Stripe, Paypal) for renewal fees
- New certificate generation with updated serial numbers
- Renewal history tracking and notifications

## Client Interface & Portal

**Certificate Verification Capabilities**

- Multi-method verification: QR code scanning, certificate number entry, three-part verification code
- Real-time verification status display
- Certificate authenticity confirmation with issuing details
- Verification history tracking
- Bulk verification capabilities for organizations

**Service Request Management**

- Online service request submission for inspections, assessments, and training
- Service request tracking and status updates
- Scheduling and rescheduling capabilities
- Request modification and cancellation options
- Priority service request options

**Document Upload/Download**

- Secure document upload with file type validation
- Document version control and history
- Bulk download capabilities
- Document categorization and tagging
- Expiry notifications for time-sensitive documents

## Inspector/Assessor Interface

**Job Order Management**

- Real-time job order assignment notifications
- Option to turn on/off new job order creation
- Job order filtering by date, location, service type, and priority
- Assignment acceptance/rejection with reason codes
- Route optimization for multiple job orders
- Job order rescheduling capabilities
- A single job order may include multiple service items, such as inspection, assessment, training, and other related activities.
- Option to save as draft
- Can't edit/delete once submitted
- Customizable job order fields based on the specific inspection type.
- Advanced filtering capabilities for efficient tracking and management of job orders.
- Automatic job order closure once the certificate or operator card has been printed.

**On-Site Inspection Tools**

- Digital checklist templates specific to inspection/assessment type
- Photo and video capture with automatic metadata (GPS, timestamp)
- OCR integration for automatic data extraction from ID cards and equipment plates
- Digital signature capture for client acknowledgment
- Offline data collection with automatic sync when online

**Real-Time Data Entry**

- Dynamic form generation based on service type
- Data validation and mandatory field enforcement
- Auto-save functionality to prevent data loss
- Voice-to-text capability for notes and observations
- Barcode scanning for equipment identification

**Inspection Approval**

- Support multi-level approval processes for inspection reports.
- Automatically notify approvers when a report is ready for their review.

**Feedback and Commenting**

- Approvers can add comments, request revisions, or provide detailed feedback before approval.

**Final Approval and Locking**

- Once fully approved, inspection reports are locked to prevent unauthorized edits or modifications.

**Submission and Approval History**

- Maintain a complete audit trail, including submission timestamps, approval milestones, and actions taken throughout the approval cycle.

## Operator Assessment Module

**Assessment Creation**

- Define assessment criteria, including theoretical knowledge tests and practical skill evaluations.

**Assessment Scheduling**

- Schedule operator assessments for both onsite and remote sessions.

**Performance Recording**

- Record assessment results, including scores, pass/fail outcomes, and evaluator feedback.

**Operator Picture Capture**

- Capture or upload an operator's photo at the time of assessment for verification purposes.

**Card Printing**

- Generate ATM-sized operator cards containing key details such as assessment results and validity dates.

**Certificate Management**

- Issue, manage, and renew operator certificates based on assessment outcomes.

**Performance Tracking**

- Track operator performance over time and generate detailed historical performance reports.

## NDT Technician Interface

**NDT-Specific Job Orders**

- NDT testing type specification (ultrasonic, radiographic, magnetic particle, etc.)
- Equipment and calibration requirements
- Safety protocol checklists
- Specialized reporting templates for different NDT methods

**Results Documentation**

- Numeric data entry with unit validation
- Graph and chart generation for test results
- Defect identification and classification
- Recommendation generation based on test outcomes
- Integration with NDT equipment for automated data capture

## Trainer Interface

**Training Session Scheduling**

- Scheduled training sessions data including attendance and assessment outcomes
- Calendar integration with availability management
- Resource booking (rooms, equipment, materials)
- Participant capacity management
- Automated reminder and confirmation system
- Waitlist management for overbooked sessions
- Microsoft Teams integration for online training
- Training/ Assessments results (certificates)

**Assessment Recording**

- Digital assessment forms with scoring algorithms
- Real-time participant progress tracking
- Pass/fail determination with criteria validation
- Individual and group performance analytics
- Remedial training recommendation system

## Supervisor Dashboard

**Approval Queue Management**

- Prioritized approval queue with SLA tracking
- Batch approval capabilities for similar items
- Approval delegation and escalation rules
- Detailed review interface with all supporting documentation
- Approval audit trail and comments system
- Transfer Job order within team

**Team Performance Tracking**

- Individual inspector/trainer performance metrics
- Productivity analysis and benchmarking
- Quality scores and client feedback correlation
- Training and development need identification
- Performance trend analysis and reporting

## System Admin

- Manage all user accounts
- Create, delete and suspend user accounts
- Access to all features

## Sticker Manager

**Automatic Lot Generation**

- The system generates sticker/tag lots in various sizes and prepares them for printing.

**Stock Issuance**

- Stickers/tags can be issued to specific regions or individual inspectors.

**Internal Transfers**

- Supervisors can transfer stickers/tags between team members as needed.

**Stock Requests and Returns**

- Regions or inspectors can request new stock, return unused items, and track availability through the system.

**Admin Oversight**

- Administrators can monitor and manage overall sticker/tag inventory in real time.

## Certificate & Operator Assessment Card Management

**Certificate Generation**

- Automatically generate certificates using predefined templates upon successful assessment completion.

**Digital Certificates**

- Issue digital certificates with QR codes for quick and secure verification.

**Certificate Repository**

- Maintain a centralized, searchable repository of all certificates, including relevant metadata for easy tracking.

**Renewal Notifications**

- Send automated alerts to notify operators and administrators of upcoming certificate renewals or expirations.

## Accountant Dashboard

**Payment Verification**

- Payment matching with job orders and invoices
- Bank statement reconciliation tools
- Payment dispute management
- Automated payment confirmation workflows
- Payment method analysis and recommendations

**Revenue Reporting**

- Real-time revenue tracking by service type, region, and time period
- Profit margin analysis
- Outstanding payment tracking and collection support
- Financial forecasting based on pipeline
- Integration with external accounting systems

## Manager/GM Dashboard/ Technical Manager

**Company-Wide Analytics**

- Executive summary dashboards with key performance indicators
- Departmental performance comparisons
- Market trend analysis and competitive positioning
- Resource utilization and capacity planning
- Strategic goal tracking and milestone monitoring

**Override Capabilities**

- Emergency approval override with justification requirements
- Certificate reprint and modification authorization
- User access management and role modifications
- System configuration changes
- Data correction and audit trail management

## Reporting & Analytics

**Report Generation**

- Generate comprehensive reports for inspections and assessments, including findings, defects, and corrective actions.

**Data Visualization**

- Interactive dashboards displaying key performance indicators (KPIs) such as inspection completion rates, defect trends, and operator performance.

**Customizable Analytics**

- Filter and analyze data by date, location, region, inspector, company, inspection category, or any other relevant criteria.
- Support detailed metrics such as upcoming expiries, expired items, and total quantities of inspections, assessments, trainings, and NDT activities, either overall or by category.

**Export Options**

- Export reports in multiple formats, including PDF, Excel, and CSV.
- Generate reports for different timeframes: daily, weekly, monthly, yearly, or custom periods.

## Activity Logs

**User Actions**

- Log user activities (login, data updates, etc.) with details like user ID, action type, timestamp, and affected data.

**System Events**

- Log critical system events (errors, warnings) with event details and timestamps.

**Storage**

- Logs are stored securely with retention policies for archiving or deletion.

**Access Control**

- Logs can only be accessed by authorized users (admin or auditors).

**Search/Filter**

- Logs can be searched and filtered by user, action type, and date.

**Export**

- Logs can be exported in CSV or JSON formats.

# Team Resources

The development of the system will involve two key resources for the duration of the project:

- **Front-End Developer**  
    Responsible for the user interfaces of the web and mobile apps, ensuring responsive, user-friendly designs, and smooth navigation.
- **Back-End Developer**  
    Responsible for the server-side logic, API development, database management, and cloud infrastructure setup. The backend will integrate with third-party APIs and ensure secure data handling and processing.

# Project Management & Communication

The project will be managed using Agile methodology, with bi-weekly sprints and regular status updates. Communication will be done via:

- Weekly check-in calls, with the possibility of twice-weekly or more frequent calls at the beginning.
- Email updates
- MS Teams for daily communications

# Assumptions and Constraints

- The UI designs (wireframes, mockups) and branding elements (logos, color schemes) must be provided and finalized by the client before development starts. Changes after this point may impact the timeline and budget.
- The client will bear all third-party costs, including hosting, payment gateway fees, and third-party software licenses.
- Any changes or additions to the project scope after the SOW is approved will result in a revised timeline and budget. Scope changes must be discussed, agreed upon, and formally documented before work begins on new tasks.
- Timely feedback from the client is essential to maintain the project schedule.
- The client will conduct UAT to ensure the system meets their business needs. The development team will address any issues found during UAT, but significant changes may require additional time and cost.
- Any custom integrations or additional features that were not originally discussed in the BRD will need to be evaluated for feasibility and will be considered out of scope unless agreed upon separately.

# Intellectual Property

## Ownership of Developed Software

The intellectual property rights of the website, including code, documentation, UI designs, and architecture, will be owned by the Client as work made for hire.

## Content Rights

Client will hold all content rights (code, UI design, text, images, logos, user data). Client is responsible for securing licenses for third-party content.

# Termination

Either party may terminate with 14 days' written notice. If Client terminates without cause, Developer is entitled to payment for work completed. Termination for cause includes material breach, significant delay, or non-payment. Confidential Information shall be returned or destroyed upon termination.
